<eesti>Autori&otilde;iguse asjatundjate komisjoni moodustanud Vabariigi Valitsuse korraldusse on tehtud muudatusi - seda Vabariigi Valitsuse 28. m&auml;rtsi 2000. a. korraldusega nr 242-k "Vabariigi Valitsuse 1. juuni 1999. a. korralduse nr 646-k "Autori&otilde;iguse asjatundjate komisjoni moodustamine" muutmine" (RTL 2000, 40, 580). </eesti>
<inglise>The Government of the Republic Order which formed the copyright committee has been amended by Government of the Republic Order No. 242-k of 28 March 2000 "Amendment of Government of the Republic Order No. </inglise>
<eesti>Autori&otilde;iguse seadusesse tehtud ning 15. veebruaril 1999. a. j&otilde;ustunud muudatuste alusel (&sect; 87 lg 1) moodustati 1999. a. autori&otilde;iguse asjatundjate komisjon (Vabariigi Valitsuse 1. juuni 1999. a. korraldus nr 646-k). </eesti>
<inglise>646-k of 1 June 1999 "Formation of Copyright Committee"" (RTL 2000, 40, 580). Based on amendments made to the Copyright Act (subsection 87 (1)) which entered into force on 15 February 1999, the copyright committee was formed in 1999 (Government of the Republic Order No. </inglise>
<eesti>Uued muudatused autori&otilde;iguse seadusesse j&otilde;ustusid k.a. algul (06.01.2000) ning nende kohaselt t&auml;psustati ka autori&otilde;iguse komisjoni puudutavaid s&auml;tteid. </eesti>
<inglise>646-k of 1 June 1999). Later amendments to the Copyright Act specifying the provisions concerning the copyright committee entered into force at the beginning of this year (06.01.2000). </inglise>
<eesti>Korralduse punkti 4 (eeln&otilde;u punkt 2) on muudetud tulenevalt komisjoni t&ouml;&ouml; parema ja efektiivsema organiseerimise vajadusest. </eesti>
<inglise>Clause 4 of the Order (clause 2 of the draft) was amended due to the need to organise the work of the committee better and more efficiently. </inglise>
<eesti>Autori&otilde;iguse seaduses on s&auml;testatud, et komisjon esitab Vabariigi Valitsusele kaks korda aastas &uuml;levaate olukorrast autori&otilde;iguse ja autori&otilde;igusega kaasnevate &otilde;iguste kaitse taseme vastavusest Eesti Vabariigi poolt v&otilde;etud rahvusvahelistele kohustustele ning autori&otilde;igusaktide kohaldamise praktikast, esitades vajaduse korral samas ettepanekuid sellealase tegevuse t&otilde;hustamiseks (&sect; 87 lg 3). </eesti>
<inglise>The Copyright Act provides that the committee shall submit an overview of the degree to which the level of protection of copyright and related rights in Estonia is in compliance with international obligations assumed by Estonia and of practical issues in the implementation of copyright legislation to the Government of the Republic twice a year and, if necessary, shall make proposals to improve activities in this field (subsection 87 (3)). </inglise>
<eesti>Komisjoni moodustanud Vabariigi Valitsuse 1. juuni 1999. a. korraldusega nr 646-k oli pandud nimetatud kohustuse t&auml;itmiseks iga aasta esimene ja neljas kvartal, s.t. esitada oleks tulnud praktiliselt kaks &uuml;levaadet j&auml;rjest (31. detsembriks ja j&auml;rgmise aasta 31. m&auml;rtsiks). </eesti>
<inglise>The terms for performing this obligation were, pursuant to Government of the Republic Order No. 646-k of 1 June 1999 which formed the committee, the first and fourth quarter every year, i.e. two overviews would have had to be submitted virtually one after another (by 31 December and 31 March of the following year). </inglise>
<eesti>See ei oleks j&auml;tnud aega komisjoni poolt tehtud ettepanekute konkretiseerimiseks ega vajalike eeln&otilde;ude korrektseks ja l&auml;bim&otilde;eldud v&auml;ljat&ouml;&ouml;tamiseks. </eesti>
<inglise>This would not have allowed enough time to elaborate the proposals made by the committee or to prepare the necessary draft acts correctly and thoroughly. </inglise>
<eesti>Samuti ei toimu paari kuu jooksul eeldatavasti suuri ja p&otilde;him&otilde;ttelisi muudatusi &uuml;le&uuml;ldises autori&otilde;igusealases olukorras, mis vajaksid p&otilde;hjalikku anal&uuml;&uuml;si Vabariigi Valitsusele esitatavas &uuml;levaates. </eesti>
<inglise>Also, it can be presumed that major changes in the principles and the general situation relating to copyright which would require in-depth analysis in the overview submitted to the Government of the Republic would not take place during just a couple of months. </inglise>
<eesti>Seega oli otstarbekam panna &uuml;levaadete esitamise t&auml;htaegadeks iga aasta teine ja neljas kvartal, kuna pooleaastaste vahedega esitatavad dokumendid saavad arvatavasti olema sisukamad ja p&otilde;hjalikumad, kui p&otilde;him&otilde;tteliselt j&auml;rjestikku esitatavad. </eesti>
<inglise>Thus, it was more practical to set the terms for the submission of overviews to be the second and fourth quarter every year as documents which are submitted after a six month pause would probably be more substantial and thorough than documents submitted one after another. </inglise>
<eesti>Samuti on nimetatud komisjoni liikmeks mittetulundus&uuml;hingu Eesti Audiovisuaalautorite Liidu juhatuse liige Allen-Illimar Putnik (korralduse eeln&otilde;u punkt nr 3). </eesti>
<inglise>Allen-Illimar Putnik, a member of the management board of the Estonian Association of Audiovisual Authors, a non-profit association, has been appointed a member of the committee (clause 3 of the draft Order). </inglise>
<eesti>Vabariigi Valitsuse 1. juuni 1999. a. korralduse nr 646-k vastuv&otilde;tmise ajaks ei olnud vastav audiovisuaalautoreid esindav organisatsioon veel loodud (&uuml;hing registreeriti 1999. a. augustis). </eesti>
<inglise>At the time when Government of the Republic Order No. 646-k of 1 June 1999 was passed, no corresponding organisation representing authors of audio-visual works had been established (the association was registered in August 1999). </inglise>
<eesti>Autori&otilde;iguse asjatundjate komisjoni idee on v&otilde;imalikult laiap&otilde;hjaline esindatus erinevate kollektiivse esindamise organisatsioonide poolt, seega peame otstarbekaks kaasata nimetatud komisjoni ka audiovisuaalsete teoste autorite esindaja. </eesti>
<inglise>The idea behind the copyright committee is to have as broad a representation of different collective management organisations as possible and we therefore consider it desirable to include a representative of authors of audio-visual works in the committee. </inglise>
