<eesti>Seaduseeln&otilde;ud </eesti>
<inglise>Draft Acts </inglise>
<eesti>Komisjoni poolt Vabariigi Valitsusele esitatava &uuml;levaate &uuml;heks eesm&auml;rgiks on ettepanekute esitamine autori&otilde;igusealases olukorra parandamiseks ka seadusandluse tasemel. </eesti>
<inglise>One of the objectives of the overview submitted to the Government of the Republic by the committee is to make proposals in order to improve the situation relating to copyright at the legislative level. </inglise>
<eesti>Eelmine &uuml;levaade esitati Vabariigi Valitsusele 1999. a. 30. detsembril ning dokumenti arutati Vabariigi Valitsuse 18. jaanuari 2000. a. istungil nr 3. </eesti>
<inglise>The previous overview was submitted to the Government of the Republic on 30 December 1999 and the document was discussed at session no. </inglise>
<eesti>Tulenevalt nimetatud istungi protokolli p&auml;evakorrapunkti nr 2 alapunktist 2 tehti Kultuuriministeeriumile koos Justiitsministeeriumiga, Siseministeeriumiga, Majandusministeeriumiga ja Rahandusministeeriumiga &uuml;lesandeks t&ouml;&ouml;tada (l&auml;htudes nimetatud &uuml;levaatest) v&auml;lja konkreetsed ettepanekud kehtivatesse &otilde;igusaktidesse muudatuste tegemise kohta. </eesti>
<inglise>3 of the Government of the Republic on 18 January 2000. According to sub-item 2 of item 2 of the minutes of this session, the Ministry of Culture together with the Ministry of Justice, the Ministry of Internal Affairs, the Ministry of Economic Affairs and the Ministry of Finance were assigned the task of preparing (based on the overview) specific proposals concerning the amendment of legislation in force at the time. </inglise>
<eesti>T&auml;naseks on p&otilde;hiliselt nimetatud ministeeriumite komisjoni t&ouml;&ouml;s osalevate esindajate ning teiste komisjoni liikmete poolt v&auml;lja t&ouml;&ouml;tatud ka "Autori&otilde;iguse seaduse muutmise seaduse" eeln&otilde;u. </eesti>
<inglise>A draft Copyright Act Amendment Act has now been prepared mostly by the people involved in the work of the committee who are representatives of those ministries and also by other members of the committee. </inglise>
<eesti>Eeln&otilde;u on koosk&otilde;lastusringi l&auml;binud (Majandus-, Rahandus-, Sise- ja Justiitsministeerium) ning Riigikantseleile esitatud Kultuuriministeeriumi 01.06.2000. a. kirjaga nr 3-6/2496. </eesti>
<inglise>The draft Act has been circulated for approval (in the Ministry of Economic Affairs, the Ministry of Finance, the Ministry of Internal Affairs and the Ministry of Justice) and submitted to the State Chancellery in communication no. </inglise>
<eesti>Nimetatud eeln&otilde;u on v&auml;lja t&ouml;&ouml;tatud m&otilde;ningate autori&otilde;iguse seaduse rakendamise praktikas esilekerkinud probleemide lahendamiseks. </eesti>
<inglise>3-6/2496 from the Ministry of Culture on 1 June 2000. The draft Act has been prepared in order to solve certain problems which have arisen in the course of implementing the Copyright Act. </inglise>
<eesti>Vabariigi Valitsusele esitatud &uuml;levaade sisaldas ka mitmeid ettepanekuid protsessinormide muutmise ja t&auml;iendamise kohta. </eesti>
<inglise>The overview submitted to the Government of the Republic also contained several proposals to amend procedural provisions. </inglise>
<eesti>L&auml;bir&auml;&auml;kimistel Justiitsministeeriumi esindajatega selgus siiski, et kuna ettevalmistamisel on mitmed uued seadustikud (uus tsiviilkohtupidamise seadustik, v&auml;&auml;rteomenetluse seadustik jne), kus need probleemid saavad lahendatud, siis ei ole hetkel otstarbekas hakata kehtivatesse protsessinormidesse muudatusi tegema. </eesti>
<inglise>However, in the course of discussions with representatives of the Ministry of Justice, it became apparent that, as several new Codes are currently being prepared (the new Code of Civil Procedure, Code of Misdemeanour Procedure, etc.) which will solve these problems, there is no real meaning at the moment to embark on amending the procedural provisions currently in force. </inglise>
<eesti>Seet&otilde;ttu ongi tegemist eeln&otilde;uga, millega planeeritakse muudatusi vaid autori&otilde;iguse seadusesse, et nende kaudu seadusi rakendavate institutsioonide t&ouml;&ouml;d veelgi t&otilde;hustada. </eesti>
<inglise>For this reason, only amendments to the Copyright Act are planned in the draft Act in order to render the work of institutions which implement Acts even more efficient. </inglise>
<eesti>Eeln&otilde;uga tehakse autori&otilde;iguse seadusesse muudatusi kolmes p&otilde;hilises probleemk&uuml;simuses: </eesti>
<inglise>The draft Act amends the Copyright Act with regard to three main problematic issues: </inglise>
<eesti>1) raham&auml;rkide kujunduse autorikaitse; </eesti>
