<eesti>Mis puudutab aga konkreetselt politseid, tolli, kohtunikke ja prokur&ouml;re, siis n&auml;iteks 10-12 mail 2000. a. korraldas EAKO nn "Tollituuri", mis h&otilde;lmas endas P&auml;rnu (Edela), V&otilde;ru (Kagu) ja Narva (Kirde) tolliinspektuure. </eesti>
<inglise>As regards the police, customs, judges and prosecutors, the Estonian Organisation for Copyright Protection organised the so-called "Customs Tour" involving P&auml;rnu (South-western), V&otilde;ru (South-eastern) and Narva (North-eastern) Customs Inspectorates on 10-12 May 2000. </inglise>
<eesti>Koolitusel osales igast inspektuurist ligikaudu 30 osav&otilde;tjat ning p&otilde;hiteemaks oli piraatkoopiate eristamine (film, muusika, interaktiivsed m&auml;ngud) ja loa olemasolu kontrollimine piiril. </eesti>
<inglise>Approximately thirty people from each inspectorate participated in the training and the main topic was the distinguishing of pirated copies (films, music, interactive games) from originals and verification of the existence of authorisation on the border. </inglise>
<eesti>&Uuml;ks seminar neile sihtgruppidele on planeeritud ka 20. ja 22. juunile 2000. aastal. </eesti>
<inglise>A seminar for these target groups is also planned for 20 and 22 June 2000. </inglise>
<eesti>Esimese p&auml;eva koolitus on m&otilde;eldud politsei- ja tolliametnikele, teine p&auml;ev kohtunikele ja prokur&ouml;ridele. </eesti>
<inglise>The first day of training is intended for police officers and customs officials and the second day for judges and prosecutors. </inglise>
<eesti>Tegemist on k&uuml;llaltki praktilise suunitlusega seminariga, kus lektoriteks on autori&otilde;igusealase temaatikaga igap&auml;evaselt oma t&ouml;&ouml;s kokku puutuvad spetsialistid, kes on k&otilde;ik &uuml;htlasi ka autori&otilde;iguse asjatundjate komisjoni liikmed. </eesti>
<inglise>This seminar has a distinctly practical orientation and the lecturers are specialists who deal with copyright-related issues in their daily work and who are all also members of the copyright committee. </inglise>
<eesti>Selle seminari n&auml;ol on j&auml;rjekordselt tegemist Phare 4MEUR projekti raames esitatud koolitustaotlusega, kuid erinevaid &otilde;igustevaldajate gruppe esindavate organisatsioonide initsiatiivil saavad koolitusprojektid kindlasti j&auml;tkuma. </eesti>
<inglise>The seminar is being organised on the basis of a petition for training submitted within the framework of the Phare 4MEUR Project but other training projects will certainly continue in the future on the initiative of organisations representing different groups of right-holders. </inglise>
<eesti>&Uuml;heks viimasel ajal p&auml;evakorrale t&otilde;usnud oluliseks teemaks on ka autori&otilde;iguste ja autori&otilde;igustega kaasnevate &otilde;iguste rikkumine internetis. </eesti>
<inglise>Infringement of copyright and related rights on the internet is an area which has also become topical recently. </inglise>
<eesti>Autori&otilde;iguste rikkumine ja piraatkoopiate m&uuml;&uuml;gilepakkumine internetis on sagenenud, mis on ka &uuml;heks paratamatuks tagaj&auml;rjeks t&auml;navapiraatluse t&otilde;kestamisele. </eesti>
<inglise>Infringement of copyright and the offer for sale of pirated copies on the internet have become more frequent, which is another of the inevitable consequences of combating piracy on the streets. </inglise>
<eesti>Kultuuriministeeriumi egiidi all toimub interneti asjatundjatega koost&ouml;&ouml;protsess, mis on tervitatav ja mille j&auml;tkamiseks on p&otilde;hilist initsiatiivi &uuml;les n&auml;idanud Eesti Autori&otilde;iguste Kaitse Organisatsioon (EAKO) ja Eesti Fonogrammitootjate &Uuml;hing (EF&Uuml;). on Eesti Autori&otilde;iguste Kaitse Organisatsioon (EAKO ja EF&Uuml;) v&auml;ga huvitatud. </eesti>
<inglise>A process of co-operation with internet experts is taking place under the auspices of the Ministry of Culture, a process which is very welcome and for which most of the initiative has been displayed by the Estonian Organisation for Copyright Protection (EOCP) and the Estonian Association of Producers of Phonograms (EAPP). </inglise>
<eesti>25. mail 2000. a. toimus esimene kohtumine &otilde;igustevaldajate esindajate (EF&Uuml; ja EAKO) ning suuremate teenusepakkujate ja internetikaubamajade esindajate vahel. </eesti>
<inglise>The first meeting of the representatives of right-holders (the EAPP and EOCP) and the representatives of major service providers and on-line shops was held on 25 May 2000. </inglise>
<eesti>Kohtumisel lepiti p&otilde;him&otilde;tteliselt kokku edasises koost&ouml;&ouml;s ning (l&auml;htudes maikuus 2000 Euroopa Liidu N&otilde;ukogu ja Parlamendi poolt vastu v&otilde;etud uue direktiivi n&otilde;uetest) hakatakse v&auml;lja t&ouml;&ouml;tama koost&ouml;&ouml;memorandumit. </eesti>
<inglise>Further co-operation was agreed upon in principle at the meeting and (based on the requirements of the new Directive adopted by the Council of Europe and the European Parliament in May 2000) the preparation of a memorandum of co-operation will commence. </inglise>
<eesti>Eelmainitud koost&ouml;&ouml; v&otilde;imaldab riigil v&auml;ltida oletatavaid kulutusi, mis tekkiksid juhul kui internet j&auml;&auml;ks stiihiliseks keskkonnaks v&auml;ljaspool t&auml;itevv&otilde;imu vaatev&auml;lja. </eesti>
<inglise>This co-operation will allow the state to avoid the expenses which would presumably occur if the internet were to remain an unregulated environment outside the authority of executive power. </inglise>
<eesti>V&auml;&auml;riks tutvustamist ka veel &uuml;ks Kultuuriministeeriumi ja Majandusministeeriumi tellimisel toimunud uurimust&ouml;&ouml; - nimelt Phare projekti "Support to European Integration Process" (No 99/C/62) raames viis Eesti Konjunktuuri Instituut (EKI) l&auml;bi uurimuse "Piraat muusikakassettide, CD'de, videote ja arvutitarkvara osakaal elanike ostudes ja elanike hinnang antud toodete turule (hinnad, toodete p&auml;ritolu, ostukohad)". </eesti>
<inglise>Another research project ordered by the Ministry of Culture and the Ministry of Economic Affairs is worth mentioning - namely, within the framework of the Phare project "Support to European Integration Process (No 99/C/62)", the Estonian Institute of Economic Research (EIER) has conducted a survey "The proportion of pirated tapes, CD-s, videos and computer software in residents' purchases and an assessment by residents of the market for such products (prices, origin of products, places of purchase)". </inglise>
<eesti>T&auml;naseks p&auml;evaks on EKI l&otilde;petanud ka uuringu anal&uuml;&uuml;si tegemise ning seda tutvustati 31. mail 2000. a. erinevatele asjaosalistele (Majandus-, Rahandus- ja Kultuuriministeeriumi esindajad, samuti oli kutsutud &otilde;igustevaldajate ja maaletoojate esindajaid). </eesti>
<inglise>The EIER has now completed its analysis of the survey and, on 31 May 2000, the results were presented to various interested parties (representatives of the Ministry of Economic Affairs, the Ministry of Finance and the Ministry of Culture, as well as representatives of right-holders and importers). </inglise>
<eesti>Tegemist oli ulatuslikuma uuringu esimese etapiga e. elanike k&uuml;sitlusega. </eesti>
<inglise>This was the first stage of a more extensive study, or opinion poll. </inglise>
<eesti>Uurimist&ouml;&ouml; p&uuml;&uuml;ab kaasa aidata &uuml;levaate loomisele salvestustoodete piraatkaubanduse ulatusest Eestis ning on suunatud intellektuaalse omandi kaitse tugevdamisele ja v&otilde;itluse t&otilde;hustamisele salvestiste salakaubanduse vastu. </eesti>
<inglise>The research is attempting to contribute to providing an overview of the extent of the trade in pirated recorded products in Estonia and is aimed at strengthening the protection of intellectual property and of implementing more efficient means of combating of illegal trade in recordings. </inglise>
<eesti>R&otilde;hutamist vajab, et selle etapi tulemused kajastavad elanike hinnanguid piraatkaubanduse leviku osas. </eesti>
<inglise>It must be emphasised that the results at this stage reflect the residents' assessment of the spread of trade in pirated goods. </inglise>
<eesti>K&uuml;sitletute eksperthinnangul ehk nende arvamusel "teiste kohta" ostab 38% eestimaalasi helikassette piraattoodetena. </eesti>
<inglise>In the opinion of people who were questioned on "other people", 38% of people living in Estonia buy pirated audio tapes. </inglise>
<eesti>Sama n&auml;itaja CD-plaatide osas on 43%, videokassettide osas 42% ja arvutitarkvara osas 40%. </eesti>
<inglise>The equivalent figure for CD-s is 43%, 42% for video tapes and 40% for computer software. </inglise>
<eesti>Tootjate ja esindusorganisatsioonide arvates ei pruugi aga uuringus kajastatavad andmed olla l&otilde;puni tegelikkusele vastavad. </eesti>
<inglise>However, producer organisations and collective management organisations believe that the information provided by the study may not reflect reality entirely correctly. </inglise>
<eesti>Tootjate hinnangul v&otilde;ib opereerida j&auml;rgnevate andmetega - 60% pakutavast muusikast, 70% videotest ning 72% arvutitarkvarast. </eesti>
<inglise>In the opinion of the producers, the following figures might be more accurate - 60% of all music offered for sale, 70 % of videos and 72% of computer software. </inglise>
<eesti>Seega on vahe elanike ja tootjate hinnangu vahel k&uuml;llaltki suur. </eesti>
<inglise>As can be seen, the discrepancy between the assessment of residents and that of producers is rather large. </inglise>
<eesti>P&otilde;hjaliku ja erinevatel allikatel p&otilde;hineva uurimist&ouml;&ouml; valmimiseks plaanibki EKI j&auml;tkata t&ouml;&ouml;d nn tootjauuringuga ning ettev&otilde;tete majandusn&auml;itajatest l&auml;htuvatel arvutustel. </eesti>
<inglise>In order to prepare thorough research which is based on various sources, the EIER plans to continue with the so-called producer study and calculations based on the economic indicators of undertakings. </inglise>
<eesti>&Auml;ra v&otilde;iks veel mainida j&auml;tkuvalt tugevnevat kolmandat sektorit ning nende tihedat koost&ouml;&ouml;d riiklike struktuuridega. </eesti>
<inglise>The continually strengthening third sector and its close co-operation with state structures should also be mentioned. </inglise>
<eesti>N&auml;iteks Eesti Filmilevitajate Liidu baasil loodi &auml;sja uus Eesti Autori&otilde;iguste Kaitse Organisatsioon (EAKO). </eesti>
<inglise>For instance, the new Estonian Organisation for Copyright Protection (EOCP) was recently established on the basis of the Estonian Association of Motion Picture Distributors. </inglise>
<eesti>EAKO esindab meelelahutus&auml;ris tegutsevaid ettev&otilde;tjaid, kes kasutavad autori&otilde;igusega kaitstud teoseid (filmi- ja fonogrammitootjad, kes on autori&otilde;igusega kaasnevate &otilde;iguste valdajad). </eesti>
