<eesti>Politsei tegevus </eesti>
<inglise>Activities of the police </inglise>
<eesti>Politsei tegevust 2000. aastal piraatkaubanduse vastu v&otilde;itlemisel v&otilde;ib nimetada k&uuml;llaltki aktiivseks. </eesti>
<inglise>In 2000, the police have acted quite vigorously in combating trade in pirated goods. </inglise>
<eesti>K&otilde;ige positiivsema arenguna v&otilde;ib siinkohal &auml;ra m&auml;rkida 2000. aasta maikuus politseipeadirektori aset&auml;itja korraldusega moodustatud t&ouml;&ouml;gruppi, kelle p&otilde;hi&uuml;lesandeks on intellektuaalse omandi rikkumiste v&auml;ljaselgitamine, vastavate meetmete rakendamine (haldus- ja kriminaalmenetluse l&auml;biviimine), koost&ouml;&ouml; organiseerimine jne. </eesti>
<inglise>The most significant development has been the formation, by an order of the deputy national police commissioner, of a working group in May 2000 to ascertain infringements of intellectual property rights, apply corresponding measures (the conduct of administrative and criminal proceedings), organise co-operation, and so on. </inglise>
<eesti>N&uuml;&uuml;dseks v&otilde;ib k&uuml;llaltki kindlalt v&auml;ita, et Kadaka Turg on tuntud juba ka rahvusvahelisel areenil ning seda enam on Tallinna politsei poolt algatatud ettev&otilde;tmine kiiduv&auml;&auml;rt. </eesti>
<inglise>It can now be said with certainty that Kadaka Market (Kadaka Turg) is internationally renowned and this renders the work undertaken by Tallinn Police even more laudable. </inglise>
<eesti>Kolme n&auml;dala jooksul Kadaka Turule ja Merekeskusesse tehtud sagedate reidide tulemusena on &auml;ra v&otilde;etud &uuml;le 14 000 v&otilde;ltsimiskahtlusega riideeseme, CD-plaadi, videokasseti, tarkvara. </eesti>
<inglise>As the result of frequent raids on Kadaka Market and Merekeskus over three weeks, over 14 000 items of clothing, CD-s, video tapes and software suspected of being counterfeit goods were seized. </inglise>
<eesti>Politsei plaanib tihedaid reide j&auml;tkata s&uuml;giseni. </eesti>
<inglise>The police intend to continue their frequent raids until the autumn. </inglise>
<eesti>Niisiis on esimesed sammud Kadaka Turul piraattoodanguga kauplemise likvideerimiseks politsei poolt olnud edukad. </eesti>
<inglise>So far, the first steps taken by the police to put an end to trade in pirated goods at Kadaka Market have been successful. </inglise>
<eesti>Ei saa aga &auml;ra unustada ohtu, et organiseeritud kuritegevus &uuml;ritab v&otilde;tta revan&scaron;i kohe, kui politseipoolne t&auml;helepanu n&otilde;rgeneb. </eesti>
<inglise>Nevertheless, it must not be forgotten that organised crime will try to advance itself again as soon as police scrutiny becomes less intense. </inglise>
<eesti>EAKO hinnangul toimuvad kaubanduses positiivsed muutused ainult sellisel juhul, kui intellektuaalse omandiga seonduv on j&auml;tkuvalt politsei huviorbiidis. </eesti>
<inglise>In the opinion of the EACP, positive changes in commerce will only take place if issues relating to intellectual property remain continually in the sphere of interest of the police. </inglise>
<eesti>Kadaka Turu alane temaatika oli p&auml;evakorras ka autori&otilde;iguse komisjoni initsiatiivil 26. mail 2000. a. toimunud &uuml;marlauakohtumisel. </eesti>
<inglise>Issues relating to Kadaka Market were also discussed at the round-table meeting on 26 May 2000 which was organised on the initiative of the copyright committee. </inglise>
<eesti>Koosolekul osalesid Tallinna Linnavolikogu, Tallinna Linnavalitsuse, Mustam&auml;e Linnaosa Valitsuse, Kesklinna Linnaosa Valitsuse, Tallinna Politseiprefektuuri ja Politseiameti esindajad ning enamus komisjoni liikmeid. </eesti>
<inglise>Representatives of Tallinn City Council, Tallinn City Government, Mustam&auml;e City District Government, Kesklinn City District Government, Tallinn Police Prefecture and the Police Board as well as most of the members of the committee participated in the meeting. </inglise>
<eesti>P&auml;evakorras oli piraatkaubandusega seonduvad probleemid (Kadaka kaubanduskeskus, Merekeskus) ning n&auml;gemus v&otilde;imalikest lahendustest - seda just l&auml;bi kauplemislubade andmise korra Tallinnas. </eesti>
<inglise>Problems relating to trade in pirated goods (the Kadaka Trade Centre, Merekeskus) and visions of possible solutions, especially by regulating the procedure for the issue of trade licences in Tallinn, were discussed. </inglise>
<eesti>P&uuml;&uuml;ti leida lahendust k&uuml;simusele, kas linnaosade poolt ettev&otilde;tetele antavate kauplemislubade kaudu oleks v&otilde;imalik (politsei tegevusele lisaks ja abiks) probleemi kontrolli alla saada. </eesti>
<inglise>The possibility of bringing the situation under control by city districts issuing trade licences to undertakings (to augment the activities of the police) was assessed. </inglise>
<eesti>Tallinnas reguleerib kauplemislubade andmist Tallinna Linnavalitsuse 29. detsembri 1998. a. m&auml;&auml;rus nr 84, millega kinnitati "Kauplemislubade v&auml;ljaandmise juhend Tallinnas". </eesti>
<inglise>In Tallinn, the issue of trade licences is regulated by Tallinn City Government Regulation No. 84 of 29 December 1998 approving the "Instructions for Issue of Trade Licences in Tallinn". </inglise>
<eesti>Juhendi punkti 2.4. alusel on loa v&auml;ljaandjal tegelikult olemas ka &otilde;igus see luba kehtetuks tunnistada. </eesti>
<inglise>Pursuant to clause 2.4. of the instructions, the issuer of a licence also has the right to declare the licence invalid. </inglise>
<eesti>N&auml;iteks lubab punkt 2.4.1. loa v&auml;ljaandjal kauplemisluba t&uuml;histada v&otilde;i kehtetuks tunnistada, loa peatada v&otilde;i l&otilde;petada, kui ei t&auml;ideta riigi ja Tallinna &otilde;igusaktidega kehtestatud n&otilde;udeid. </eesti>
<inglise>For instance, pursuant to clause 2.4.1, the issuer of a trade licence has the right to revoke the licence or declare it invalid, suspend it or terminate it if requirements established by Estonian or Tallinn legislation are not met. </inglise>
<eesti>Kohtumisel lepiti kokku, et &otilde;igustevaldajaid esindavate organisatsioonide kaasabil &uuml;ritatakse (enne &otilde;igusaktide t&auml;iendamist) kehtivaid s&auml;tteid praktikas kasutada ning &uuml;ritada tegutsemislubade andmise ja kehtetuks tunnistamise kaudu tekkinud olukorda omakorda parandada (s.h. muusikateoste avaliku esitamisega seonduv). </eesti>
<inglise>It was agreed at the meeting that (before amending legislation) an attempt will be made to put the existing provisions into practice with the help of collective management organisations and to improve the current situation (including issues relating to the public performance of musical works) through the issue and revocation of operating licences. </inglise>
<eesti>BSA (Business Software Alliance) hinnangul aga on just viimastel kuudel olnud m&auml;rgata tendentsi, et tarkvarapiraatlusega soovitakse tegeleda &uuml;ha v&auml;hem. </eesti>
<inglise>According to the BSA (Business Software Alliance), a tendency has been noticed in recent months whereby software piracy is gradually losing its appeal. </inglise>
<eesti>P&otilde;hjuseid on selleks toodud mitmeid, n&auml;iteks: teised prioriteedid (varavastased kuriteod jms), ajanappus jms. asjaolud. </eesti>
<inglise>Several reasons have been suggested for such a development, for example: other priorities (criminal offences against property, etc.), lack of time, and other similar circumstances. </inglise>
<eesti>Keskkriminaalpolitsei on isegi asunud seisukohale, et nende tegevusega tarkvarapiraatluse vastu v&otilde;itlemine ei seondu. </eesti>
<inglise>The Central Criminal Police have even adopted the position that combating software piracy is not relevant to their activities. </inglise>
<eesti>Politseiprefektuurid on v&auml;ljendanud oma seisukohti, et nende huviks ei ole tegeleda haldus&otilde;iguserikkumise asjadega (peamine tarkvarapiraatlusega seonduv &otilde;igusrikkumine seisnebki aga juriidiliste isikute poolt tarkvara ebaseaduslikus valdamises v&otilde;i kasutamises arvutites), vaid kriminaalasjadega. </eesti>
<inglise>Police prefectures have expressed the opinion that their interests do not lie with pursuing matters of administrative offences (although the offence most often associated with software piracy is the illegal possession or use of software in computers by legal persons) but criminal matters. </inglise>
<eesti>Sama seisukohta on toetanud ka Keskkriminaalpolitsei. </eesti>
<inglise>The Central Criminal Police has supported this point of view. </inglise>
<eesti>Samas ei tunta tegelikult aga huvi ka tarkvarapiraatlusega ja arvutite kasutamisega seotud kuritegude uurimise vastu. </eesti>
<inglise>At the same time, interest in investigating criminal offences relating to software piracy and the use of computers is waning. </inglise>
<eesti>Selliseid arvamusi on kahjuks viimasel ajal avaldatud ka ajakirjanduses politseiasutuste endi poolt. </eesti>
<inglise>Unfortunately, similar opinions have been expressed by police authorities in the press. </inglise>
<eesti>Tuleb aga ka arvestada, et politseiametnike koolitus just selles valdkonnas on siiani puudulik, kuid l&auml;hemasse tulevikku on juba planeeritud sellealase t&auml;iend&otilde;ppe teostamine. </eesti>
<inglise>It should also be taken into account that the training of police officers in this field has been rather poor so far but relevant in-service training is planned for the near future. </inglise>
<eesti>Riik peaks siiski p&ouml;&ouml;rama piisavalt t&auml;helepanu sellele, et k&otilde;ik riigis aset leidvad &otilde;iguserikkumised (nii haldus&otilde;iguserikkumised kui kuriteod) saaksid avastatud, t&otilde;kestatud ja s&uuml;&uuml;dlased vastutusele v&otilde;etud. </eesti>
<inglise>Nevertheless, the state should make sufficient effort to ensure that all offences committed in the country (both administrative and criminal offences) are discovered or prevented and that charges are brought against the guilty parties. </inglise>
<eesti>Samas sooviksime aga siiski r&otilde;hutada, et &uuml;ldine olukord autori&otilde;iguste j&auml;rgimisega on Eestis alates 2000. aasta algusest muutunud m&otilde;ningal m&auml;&auml;ral paremaks ning seda kindlasti ka politseipoolse tegevuse aktiviseerumisest tulenevalt. </eesti>
<inglise>Still, it should be emphasised that, since the beginning of the year 2000, the general situation relating to adherence to copyright in Estonia has improved to a certain extent, and this is definitely also due to more intense action on the part of the police. </inglise>
<eesti>Asjaolu, et m&otilde;ningate autori&otilde;igusealaste rikkumiste puhul nende initsiatiiv on m&otilde;ningal m&auml;&auml;ral v&auml;henenud, ei v&auml;henda oluliselt tehtud t&ouml;&ouml; t&auml;htsust. </eesti>
<inglise>The fact that their initiatives have decreased a little when it comes to certain copyright-related violations does not diminish the importance of the work done. </inglise>
<eesti>Probleemiks on teatud m&auml;&auml;ral senini j&auml;&auml;nud Ida-Virumaa, kus n&auml;iteks Sillam&auml;el ja Kohtla-J&auml;rvel on autori&otilde;iguste kaitsmine j&auml;&auml;nud tahaplaanile. </eesti>
<inglise>The county of Ida-Virumaa is still a problem as not too much attention is paid to the protection of copyright in Sillam&auml;e or Kohtla-J&auml;rve, for example. </inglise>
<eesti>Siiski on ka selles piirkonnas 2000. aasta jooksul senisest suuremat t&auml;helepanu p&ouml;&ouml;ratud piraatluse probleemi lahendamiseks (t&ouml;&ouml; t&otilde;hustamise n&auml;itena v&otilde;iks tuua KrK &sect; 280 alusel algatatud seitset (7) kriminaalasja). </eesti>
<inglise>Nevertheless, during the year 2000, more effort than ever before has been put in there to try to solve the problem of piracy (an example would be the proceedings which have been initiated with regard to seven (7) criminal matters on the basis of &sect; 280 of the Criminal Code). </inglise>
<eesti>1999. aastal kokku v&otilde;ttis politsei &auml;ra 53 052 &uuml;hikut piraattooteid (s.h. audiokassette 2987, CD-plaate 26 137, videokassette 18 756, tarkvara 1261). </eesti>
<inglise>In 1999, the police seized a total of 53 052 pirated items (including 2987 audio tapes, 26 137 CD-s, 18 756 video tapes, and 1261 items of software). </inglise>
<eesti>Autori&otilde;iguselastes rikkumistes koostas politsei 73 protokolli ning algatas 42 kriminaalasja. </eesti>
