<eesti>Tolli tegevus </eesti>
<inglise>Activities of customs authorities </inglise>
<eesti>Tolli tegevusest, rikkumistest, 1999. a. statistikast on andnud hea &uuml;levaate Rahandusministeeriumi poolt esitatud aruanne tolli tegevuse kohta (Vabariigi Valitsuse 18. jaanuari 2000. a. istungi protokolli nr 3 p&auml;evakorrapunkti 2 alapunkti 3 t&auml;itmine). </eesti>
<inglise>A comprehensive overview of the activities of customs authorities, of customs violations and of customs statistics for 1999 was provided in the report on the activities of customs authorities presented by the Ministry of Finance (pursuant to sub-item 3 of item 2 of minutes no. 3 of the Government of the Republic session of 18 January 2000). </inglise>
<eesti>Seal kajastatud andmeid ei ole seega m&otilde;tet t&auml;ies mahus siinkohal reprodutseerida. </eesti>
<inglise>There is therefore no point in reproducing the information provided there in full here. </inglise>
<eesti>Siiski m&otilde;ned olulisemad punktid peaks v&auml;lja tooma. </eesti>
<inglise>However, certain points of significant importance should be emphasised. </inglise>
<eesti>V&auml;idetavalt on &otilde;igusi rikkuva kauba avastamine t&auml;na k&uuml;llaltki juhuslik, s.t. avastamine s&otilde;ltub tolliinspektori kogemusest, lojaalsusest ja initsiatiivist, kontaktisiku aktiivsusest jne. </eesti>
<inglise>Arguably, the discovery of goods infringing rights happens at the moment rather by chance, i.e. discoveries depend on the experience, loyalty and initiative of the customs inspectors, on whether the contact persons are active, etc. </inglise>
<eesti>Sellest n&auml;htub, et p&otilde;hik&uuml;simus taandub ikkagi tolliametnike koolitusvajadusele. </eesti>
<inglise>This means that the main issue is the training needs of customs officials. </inglise>
<eesti>Tolliameti j&auml;relevalveosakonna koolitusspetsialistid on teinud palju t&ouml;&ouml;d tolliametnike koolitamisel, kuid tulemused on Eesti Autori&otilde;iguste Kaitse Organisatsiooni (EAKO) hinnangul j&auml;&auml;nud kesisteks. </eesti>
<inglise>The training specialists of the supervisory department of the Customs Board have done a lot of work to provide training for customs officials but the results have not been very impressive according to the Estonian Organisation of Copyright Protection (EACP). </inglise>
<eesti>EAKO toob positiivse n&auml;itena v&auml;lja Kagu tolliinspektuuri ning avaldab arvamust, et kui toll t&ouml;&ouml;taks intellektuaalse omandi rikkumistega veelgi t&otilde;sisemalt, v&auml;heneks selle tulemusel koormus teistele ametkondadele. </eesti>
<inglise>The EACP states that the South-eastern Customs Inspectorate sets a positive example and expresses the opinion that if customs authorities treated infringements of intellectual property rights even more seriously, this would lead to a decrease in the workload of other agencies. </inglise>
<eesti>1999. a. kokku avastati juhtumeid 169, neist &otilde;iguste rikkumisi 154 puhul. </eesti>
<inglise>In 1999, a total of 169 cases were discovered, and of these rights were violated in 154 cases. </inglise>
<eesti>Piraatkaupa v&otilde;eti &auml;ra 851 &uuml;hikut (muusikat 546, tarkvara 193, filmid 112 &uuml;hikut). </eesti>
<inglise>851 items of pirate production were seized (546 music items, 193 software items, and 112 film items). </inglise>
<eesti>2000. a. esimese viie kuuga on Tolliametist saadud informatsiooni p&otilde;hjal intellektuaalse omandi alased andmed j&auml;rgmised: </eesti>
<inglise>According to information obtained from the Customs Board, the situation concerning intellectual property during the first five months of the year 2000 was as follows: </inglise>
<eesti>1) haldus&otilde;iguserikkumise menetlusi algatatud 100 (5 korral tegemist piraatkoopiatega, &uuml;lej&auml;&auml;nud v&otilde;ltsitud kauba juhtumid); </eesti>
<inglise>1) proceedings have been initiated in 100 matters concerning administrative offences (5 cases involve pirated copies where the remainder are cases of counterfeit goods); </inglise>
<eesti>2) kriminaalmenetlusi algatatud ei ole; </eesti>
<inglise>2) no criminal proceedings have been initiated; </inglise>
<eesti>3) &auml;rav&otilde;etud kauba kogus kokku (piraat- ja v&otilde;ltsitud kaup) - 26 634 &uuml;hikut. </eesti>
<inglise>3) the total amount of goods seized (pirated and counterfeit goods) - 26 634 items. </inglise>
<eesti>1.2.3. </eesti>
<inglise>1.2.3. </inglise>
<eesti>Kohtute tegevus </eesti>
<inglise>Activities of courts </inglise>
<eesti>Kohtunike puhulgi on suurimaks probleemkohaks v&auml;hene autori&otilde;igusealane koolitus. </eesti>
<inglise>For judges, the issue that causes most problems is, again, insufficient training in the field of copyright. </inglise>
<eesti>Analoogselt politsei ja tolli koolitusele hakatakse ka kohtuv&otilde;imu t&auml;iendamisega aktiivsemalt tegelema. </eesti>
<inglise>As is the case for the police and customs authorities, judicial authorities will also be provided with further instruction and training. </inglise>
<eesti>Kohtute tegevust k&auml;sitlevas peat&uuml;kis Vabariigi Valitsusele 1999. a. detsembris esitatud &uuml;levaates peatuti pikemalt kahel probleemil - autori&otilde;igusealastes kohtuasjades eksperthinnangu andmist ning halduskaristuse m&auml;&auml;ramiseks s&auml;testatud 2-kuulisel t&auml;htajal. </eesti>
<inglise>In the chapter on the activities of courts in the overview submitted to the Government of the Republic in December 1999, two problems were discussed at length - the provision of expert assessment in court cases relating to copyright and the two-month time-limit prescribed for the imposition of administrative penalties. </inglise>
<eesti>Nagu eespool mainitud, on viimane nimetatud k&uuml;simustest juba leidnud lahenduse Riigikogu menetluses olevas "Haldus&otilde;iguserikkumiste seadustiku, kriminaalkoodeksi, kriminaalmenetluse koodeksi ja tolliseaduse muutmise seaduse" eeln&otilde;us (eeln&otilde;u nr 33-SE). </eesti>
<inglise>As mentioned above, the latter issue has been resolved in the draft Code of Administrative Offences, Criminal Code, Code of Criminal Procedure and Customs Act Amendment Act (draft Act 33-SE) which is currently in the legislative proceeding of the Riigikogu. </inglise>
<eesti>Mis puudutab spetsialisti arvamust, ekspertiisi piraatlusk&uuml;simustes, siis "Autori&otilde;iguse seaduse muutmise seaduse" eeln&otilde;u v&auml;ljat&ouml;&ouml;tamise k&auml;igus arutati nimetatud probleemi seadusandliku lahendamise v&otilde;imalust. </eesti>
<inglise>As regards the opinion of specialists, or expert analysis in issues relating to piracy, the possibility of solving the problem by legislative means was discussed in the course of preparing the draft Copyright Act Amendment Act. </inglise>
<eesti>L&auml;bir&auml;&auml;kimistel Justiitsministeeriumi karistus&otilde;iguse osakonna esindajatega aga ei peetud vastavate muudatuste sisseviimist kehtivatesse &otilde;igusaktidesse vajalikuks. </eesti>
<inglise>However, in the course of talks with representatives of the Penal Law Department of the Ministry of Justice, the corresponding amendments to legislation currently in force were deemed unnecessary. </inglise>
<eesti>Kohtule ei saa ette kirjutada, millise organisatsiooni esindajaid ta kohtuasjas ekspertidena peab kasutama. </eesti>
<inglise>Courts cannot be told which representatives of which organisations should be used as experts in court cases. </inglise>
<eesti>Siiski on seni kohtud k&uuml;llaltki paljudel erikonfiskeerimise juhtudel toetunud just esindusorganisatsioonide poolt antud hinnangule. </eesti>
<inglise>Still, in a considerably large number of seizure cases, the courts have relied on the assessment provided by the collective management organisations. </inglise>
<eesti>Tegemist v&otilde;ib olla m&otilde;nes m&otilde;ttes kompromissiga kohtu poolt (saades aru, et praktiliselt on esindusorganisatsioonid praegu k&otilde;ige kompetentseimad isikud piraattoodete hindamisel). </eesti>
<inglise>This may be a sort of a compromise on the part of the courts (as they understand that the collective management organisations are actually the most competent persons to assess pirated products). </inglise>
<eesti>Siiski - juhtudel, kui hinnangut andnud ekspert ei ole kannatanute esindajana protsessiosaliseks (e. ei ole asjast huvitatud pooleks), peaks kohtud seda praktikat ka kindlasti j&auml;tkama. </eesti>
<inglise>Nevertheless, in cases where the expert who provides the assessment does not participate in the proceedings as the representative of the victims (i.e. is not an interested person), the courts should definitely continue this practice. </inglise>
<eesti>BSA esindaja s&otilde;nul on praktikas tekkinud probleeme sellega, milline kohus saadab otsuse erikonfiskeerimise t&auml;ideviimiseks t&auml;itevosakonnale. </eesti>
<inglise>According to a representative of the BSA there have been problems in practice as to which court should send a judgment concerning seizure to the enforcement department to be executed. </inglise>
<eesti>Kohtute endi poolt on viidatud peamiselt sellele, et seadused ei s&auml;testa seda &uuml;heselt. </eesti>
<inglise>The courts themselves have referred to the fact that this is not uniformly provided for by law. </inglise>
<eesti>&Uuml;ldiste p&otilde;him&otilde;tete kohaselt peaks erikonfiskeerimise otsuse t&auml;itmiseks saatma otsuse teinud kohus. </eesti>
<inglise>Generally, the court which makes a judgment concerning seizure should send the judgment to be executed. </inglise>
<eesti>Samas on n&auml;iteks Tallinna Ringkonnakohus asunud seisukohale, et erikonfiskeerimise otsus, mille nemad on teinud, tuleb t&auml;itmiseks saata kas esimese astme kohtu v&otilde;i haldus&otilde;iguserikkumise protokolli koostaja enda poolt. </eesti>
<inglise>However, the Tallinn Circuit Court, for instance, has adopted the position that if it makes a judgment concerning seizure, it should be the court of first instance or the person who prepared the administrative offence report who should send the judgment to be executed. </inglise>
<eesti>Seega tuleks &uuml;he v&otilde;imalusena k&otilde;ne alla vastava k&uuml;simuse lahendamine Justiitsministeeriumil enda poolt v&otilde;i hoopiski seaduses v&otilde;i m&otilde;nes madalamalseisvas &otilde;igusaktis fikseerida erikonfiskeerimise otsuse t&auml;itmise kord. </eesti>
<inglise>Thus, this issue could possibly be solved by the Ministry of Justice or the procedure for the execution of judgments concerning seizure could be provided for in an Act or legislation with lower authority. </inglise>
<eesti>II ETTEPANEKUD VABARIIGI VALITSUSELE </eesti>
<inglise>II PROPOSALS TO THE GOVERNMENT OF THE REPUBLIC </inglise>
<eesti>2.1. </eesti>
<inglise>2.1. </inglise>
<eesti>Seadusandlus </eesti>
<inglise>Legislation </inglise>
<eesti>Nagu ka &uuml;laltoodust n&auml;htub, on mitmed esimeses &uuml;levaates esitatud ettepanekud leidnud k.a. I poolaasta jooksul kajastamist kas "Autori&otilde;iguse seaduse muutmise seaduse" eeln&otilde;us v&otilde;i juba Riigikogu menetluses olevas eeln&otilde;us. </eesti>
<inglise>As described above, several proposals submitted in the first overview have been reflected in the draft Copyright Act Amendment Act or draft legislation which is already in the legislative proceeding of the Riigikogu. </inglise>
<eesti>Samuti langesid esialgsetest plaanidest v&auml;lja m&otilde;ningad protsessinorme puudutavad vajalikud s&auml;tted, kuna l&auml;bir&auml;&auml;kimistel Justiitsministeeriumiga ei leidnud need hetkel poolehoidu. </eesti>
<inglise>Also, it has been decided that certain procedural provisions should not be adopted as these provisions were not approved in negotiations with the Ministry of Justice. </inglise>
<eesti>J&auml;rgnevalt l&uuml;hikokkuv&otilde;te sellest, millised 1999. a. detsembris esitatud &uuml;levaate II osa "Ettepanekud Vabariigi Valitsusele. </eesti>
<inglise>The following is a brief summary which sets out the issues presented in Part II of the overview submitted in December 1999 "Proposals to the Government of the Republic. </inglise>
<eesti>2.1. "Seadusandlus"" toodud punktidest on erineval viisil lahenduse leidnud. </eesti>
<inglise>2.1. "Legislation"" which have been resolved by various means. </inglise>
<eesti>2.1.1. "Protsessinormid seoses TRIPS'iga" ei leidnud (nagu &uuml;lalpool mainitud) l&auml;bir&auml;&auml;kimistel Justiitsministeeriumiga l&otilde;plikku heakskiitu, kuid uute protsessikoodeksite j&otilde;ustumisega peaks k&otilde;ik &uuml;les j&auml;&auml;nud probleemid saama lahendatud. </eesti>
<inglise>2.1.1. "Procedural provisions relating to TRIPS" was not granted final approval in the negotiations with the Ministry of Justice (as mentioned above) but, with the entry into force of new procedural codes, all the remaining problems should be solved. </inglise>
<eesti>2.1.2. "F&uuml;&uuml;silisest isikust ettev&otilde;tjad" (e. kas f&uuml;&uuml;silisest isikust ettev&otilde;tjad peavad saama karistatud kriminaal- v&otilde;i halduskorras) - seadustesse ei peetud vajalikuks teha sellealaseid muudatusi, kuna JM ekspertide s&otilde;nul saab siin olla vaid &uuml;hene lahendus - f&uuml;&uuml;silisest isikust ettev&otilde;tja vastutab vaid kriminaalkorras. </eesti>
<inglise>2.1.2. "Sole proprietors" (i.e. whether sole proprietors should be punished by way of criminal or administrative procedure) - corresponding amendments to legislation were not deemed necessary as, according to experts from the Ministry of Justice, there can be only one solution - sole proprietors are held liable only pursuant to criminal procedure. </inglise>
<eesti>2.1.3. "Piraattoodangu hoidmise eest ei saa karistada" - probleem peaks leidma lahenduse "Autori&otilde;iguse seaduse muutmise seaduse" eeln&otilde;uga (&sect; 4). </eesti>
<inglise>2.1.3. "No possibility to punish for storage of pirate production" - this problem should be solved in the draft Copyright Act Amendment Act (&sect; 4). </inglise>
<eesti>2.1.4. "Halduskaristuse m&auml;&auml;ramise t&auml;htaeg" - eeln&otilde;u nr 33-SE (Riigikogu menetluses) teeb haldus&otilde;iguserikkumiste seadustikku vastavad parandused, mille tulemusena pikeneb halduskaristuse m&auml;&auml;ramise t&auml;htaeg. </eesti>
<inglise>2.1.4. "Term for imposition of administrative punishment" - draft Act no. 33-SE (in the legislative proceeding of the Riigikogu) will make the corresponding amendments to the Code of Administrative Offences as a result of which the term for the imposition of administrative punishments will be extended. </inglise>
<eesti>2.1.5. "Ebaseaduslikult muusikateoseid kasutavad &auml;ri&uuml;hingud" - kuna tegemist on paljuski teavitamisprobleemiga ning Kultuuriministeeriumis 26. mail 2000. a. toimunud koosolekul, kus viibisid ka Tallina Linnavalitsuse ja Tallinna Linnavolikogu esindajad, saavutati p&otilde;him&otilde;tteliselt kokkulepe koost&ouml;&ouml;ks &otilde;iguste valdajate esindajate (antud juhul Eesti Autorite &Uuml;hing) ja tegutsemislubade v&auml;ljaandjate (linnaosa valitsused) vahel. </eesti>
<inglise>2.1.5. "Companies which use musical works unlawfully" - the problem is largely concerned with notification and, at a meeting held at the Ministry of Culture on 26 May 2000 with representatives of Tallinn City Government and Tallinn City Council, an agreement was reached in principle for co-operation between the representatives of right-holders (in this case, the Estonian Authors' Society) and the issuers of operating licences (governments of city districts). </inglise>
<eesti>J&auml;&auml;b ka v&otilde;imalus, et muudetakse Tallinna Linnavalitsuse 29. detsembri 1998. a. m&auml;&auml;rust nr 84, millega kinnitati "Kauplemislubade v&auml;ljaandmise juhend Tallinnas" lisades nende organisatsioonide nimekirja, kellelt peab olema kauplemisloa v&auml;ljaandmiseks koosk&otilde;lastus, ka Eesti Autorite &Uuml;hing. </eesti>
<inglise>There is also the possibility that Tallinn City Government Regulation No. 84 of 29 December 1998 approving the "Instructions for Issue of Trade Licences in Tallinn" will be amended by adding the Estonian Authors' Society to the list of organisations whose approval must be obtained for the issue of a trade licence. </inglise>
<eesti>2.1.7. "Ettev&otilde;tte ruumidesse sisenemine ning piraattarkvaral olevate andmete kaitse" - ettev&otilde;tte ruumidesse sisenemise korda puudutati ka kohtumisel Justiitsministeeriumiga, kuid sealsed eksperdid (karistus&otilde;iguse osakond) ei pidanud v&otilde;imalikuks vastavasisulisi muudatusi kehtivatesse &otilde;igusaktidesse teha. </eesti>
<inglise>2.1.7. "Entering the premises of enterprises and the protection of data on pirated software" - the procedure for entering the premises of enterprises was discussed at the meeting with the Ministry of Justice but experts from the Ministry (from the Penal Law Department) did not deem it possible to make corresponding amendments to legislation currently in force. </inglise>
<eesti>Kui j&otilde;ustub hetkel v&auml;ljat&ouml;&ouml;tatav "V&auml;&auml;rteomenetluse seadustik", siis nimetatud k&uuml;simuses peaks tulevikus olema v&otilde;imalus kasutada ka k&otilde;nealuste rikkumiste puhul kriminaalmenetluses kasutatavat l&auml;biotsimist. </eesti>
<inglise>When the Code of Misdemeanour Procedure which is currently being prepared enters into force, it should also become possible to use searches used in criminal procedure in these cases. </inglise>
<eesti>Veel t&auml;nini on &uuml;leval m&otilde;ned probleemid, mis vajavad muudatusi &otilde;igusaktides. </eesti>
<inglise>There are still some problems which call for amendments to legislation. </inglise>
<eesti>Nagu ka eelmises &uuml;levaates tegelikult nimetati, on praktiliselt kogu seadusandlik baas piraatluse vastu v&otilde;itlemiseks olemas ning enne j&auml;rgmiste muudatuste kallale asumist peaks proovima olemasolevaid s&auml;tteid kasutada. t&otilde;lgendada, ellu rakendada. </eesti>
<inglise>As mentioned in the previous overview, virtually the entire legal basis needed to combat piracy already exists and, prior to making any more amendments, an attempt should be made to use, interpret and apply the existing provisions. </inglise>
<eesti>Siinkohal tooks siiski (lisaks eelmisest korrast &uuml;les j&auml;&auml;nud protsessinormidele) m&otilde;ned vajakaj&auml;&auml;mised, mis tulevikus arvatavasti lahendamist vajaksid. </eesti>
<inglise>The following are certain deficiencies (in addition to procedural provisions still yet to be resolved) which probably need to be addressed in the future. </inglise>
<eesti>2.1.1. </eesti>
<inglise>2.1.1. </inglise>
<eesti>Arvutis&uuml;steemi m&otilde;iste </eesti>
<inglise>The definition of computer system </inglise>
<eesti>Autori&otilde;iguse seadus v&otilde;imaldab erikonfiskeerida haldus&otilde;iguserikkumise toimepanemise vahendina arvutis&uuml;steemi. </eesti>
<inglise>The Copyright Act permits the seizure of a computer system used as the object to commit an administrative offence. </inglise>
<eesti>Samas ei ole &uuml;heski seaduses lahti kirjutatud arvutis&uuml;steemi m&otilde;iste. </eesti>
<inglise>However, the definition of 'computer system' is not explained in any Act. </inglise>
<eesti>Kuiv&otilde;rd tegemist on siiski olulise k&uuml;simusega ehk milline vara v&otilde;ib kuuluda erikonfiskeerimisele haldus&otilde;iguserikkumise asjas, oleks selle t&auml;psustamine ja lahtikirjutamine seaduses h&auml;davajalik. </eesti>
<inglise>As this question is rather significant, i.e. what property may be seized in a matter regarding an administrative offence, it is essential that it should be specified and explained in an Act. </inglise>
<eesti>2.1.2. </eesti>
<inglise>2.1.2. </inglise>
<eesti>Haldus&otilde;iguserikkumise toimepanemise vahendi erikonfiskeerimine s&otilde;ltumata karistuse kohaldamisest </eesti>
<inglise>Seizure of the means used to commit an administrative offence regardless of the imposition of punishment </inglise>
<eesti>Praktikas on kujunenud v&auml;lja olukord, kus kohtud on leidnud, et asjas menetluse l&otilde;petamisel ja isiku karistusest vabastamisel ei ole v&otilde;imalik kohaldada &otilde;iguserikkumiseks kasutatud tehniliste vahendite jms. erikonfiskeerimist. </eesti>
<inglise>In practice, a situation has developed where courts have found that if proceedings regarding a matter are terminated and the person is released from punishment, it is not possible to seize any equipment, etc., used to commit the offence. </inglise>
<eesti>Selline olukord on lubamatu, sest tihti on tegemist vahenditega, mis on kas kohandatud v&otilde;i mida on otseselt kasutatud &otilde;iguserikkumise toimepanemiseks. </eesti>
<inglise>Such a situation is unacceptable because often the equipment has either been adapted or directly used to commit an offence. </inglise>
<eesti>Samuti on v&auml;ga sageli tuvastatav haldus&otilde;iguserikkumise toimepanemise vahend, kuid erikonfiskeerimist ei kohaldata menetluse l&otilde;petamise ettek&auml;&auml;ndel. </eesti>
<inglise>Also, the object used to commit an offence is very frequently determined but seizure is not applied under the pretext of the termination of proceedings. </inglise>
<eesti>Kohtutel peaks olema v&auml;hemalt v&otilde;imalus (&otilde;igus) erikonfiskeerida &otilde;igustrikkuvaks k&auml;itumiseks kasutatud vahendid. </eesti>
<inglise>The courts should at least have the opportunity (the right) to seize objects used to commit offences. </inglise>
<eesti>Kohtud ise on oma praktikas asunud seisukohale, et juriidilise isiku vastutuse puhul peab selline v&otilde;imalus olema s&auml;testatud eriseadustes. </eesti>
<inglise>The courts have adopted the position that, in the case of liability of legal persons, such an opportunity must be provided for in specific Acts. </inglise>
<eesti>Sellest tulenevalt peaks autori&otilde;igusega seotud &otilde;iguserikkumise asjades haldus&otilde;iguserikkumise toimepanemiseks kasutatud vahendite erikonfiskeerimise v&otilde;imalikkus (s&otilde;ltumata karistuse kohaldamisest) olema fikseeritud autori&otilde;iguse seaduses. </eesti>
<inglise>Therefore, in matters regarding offences related to copyright, the opportunity to seize objects used to commit an administrative offence (regardless of the imposition of punishment) should be provided for in the Copyright Act. </inglise>
<eesti>2.1.4. </eesti>
<inglise>2.1.4. </inglise>
<eesti>Piraatkoopiate saatus, kui s&uuml;&uuml;distuskokkuv&otilde;tet v&otilde;i haldus&otilde;iguserikkumise protokolli ei koostata </eesti>
<inglise>The fate of pirated copies if no summary of charges or administrative offence report is prepared </inglise>
<eesti>Praktikas on t&otilde;usetunud k&uuml;simus selle kohta, mis juhtub, kui kriminaalasjas s&uuml;&uuml;distuskokkuv&otilde;tet v&otilde;i haldus&otilde;iguserikkumise asjas haldus&otilde;iguserikkumise protokolli ei koostata, kuid asjas on &auml;ra v&otilde;etud n&auml;iteks piraatkoopiad. </eesti>
<inglise>In practice, the question has been raised as to what happens if no summary of charges is prepared in a criminal matter or no administrative offence report is prepared in a matter regarding an administrative offence but if, for instance, pirated copies have been seized in the course of the matter. </inglise>
<eesti>Kohtud ei v&otilde;ta &uuml;ldjuhul selliseid asju oma menetlusse, sest puudub protsessuaalne dokument, mille alusel asi kohtunikule lahendamisele saadetakse. </eesti>
<inglise>The courts generally do not take on such matters as the procedural document on the basis of which the matter is forwarded to a judge for adjudication is missing. </inglise>
<eesti>Sellest tulenevalt peaks seadus ka s&auml;testama, millise dokumendi alusel ja kes on p&auml;dev lahendama vastavaid k&uuml;simusi (n&auml;iteks politseiasutuse juht ise v&otilde;etuse akti alusel vms.). </eesti>
<inglise>Therefore, the law should also provide for the documents on the basis of which such matters can be resolved and the persons competent to resolve such matters (for example, the head of the police authority on the basis of a seizure report, etc.). </inglise>
<eesti>P&otilde;him&otilde;tteliselt on tegemist ka eelmises &uuml;levaates kirjeldatud probleemiga (punkti 2.1.1. alapunkti 2 all). </eesti>
<inglise>In principle, this is a problem which was also described in the previous overview (in sub-point 2 of point 2.1.1). </inglise>
<eesti>Probleem ei leidnud koosk&otilde;lastatud lahendust l&auml;bir&auml;&auml;kimistel Justiitsministeeriumiga ning seet&otilde;ttu peab nimetatud k&uuml;simusega veel p&otilde;hjalikumalt tegelema. </eesti>
<inglise>A solution to the problem could not be found in the course of negotiations with the Ministry of Justice and, therefore, the issue needs to be addressed more thoroughly. </inglise>
<eesti>2.2. </eesti>
<inglise>2.2. </inglise>
<eesti>Seaduste rakendamine </eesti>
<inglise>Implementation of Acts </inglise>
<eesti>Eelmises &uuml;levaates esitati ettepanekuid ka seaduste rakendamise osas olukorra parandamiseks. </eesti>
<inglise>In the previous overview, a number of proposals were submitted to improve the implementation of Acts. </inglise>
<eesti>Seaduste rakendamise osas tehtud ettepanekute t&auml;itmisest on siiski raskem anda t&auml;pset &uuml;levaadet, kuna tegemist on palju laiemahaardelise probleemistikuga, mille puhul ette v&otilde;etud meetmete efektiivsus selgub pikema protsessi tulemusel. </eesti>
<inglise>However, it is more difficult to provide an exact overview of the degree to which proposals regarding the implementation of Acts have been accepted due to the larger scale of the problems and the fact that the efficiency of measures taken will become apparent only in the long term. </inglise>
<eesti>Seega saab vaid veelkord mainida arvukaid koolitusprogramme ja v&auml;lisabiprojekte nii erialaspetsialistidele kui ka laiemale &uuml;ldsusele. </eesti>
<inglise>Because of this, only the numerous training programmes and foreign aid projects both for specialists and the general public can be mentioned. </inglise>
<eesti>Mis puudutab levitalituse koosseisu (sealhulgas k.a. alguses loodud meedia- ja autori&otilde;iguse osakonna) t&auml;iendamist (punkt 2.2.3.), siis selles osas peaks leevendust tooma aasta 2001, mil eelarvesse planeeritakse vahendeid kohtade t&auml;itmiseks. </eesti>
<inglise>As regards increasing the staff of the Media Division (including the Media and Copyright Department established at the beginning of this year) (point 2.2.3.), the situation should be alleviated in 2001 when funds will be included in the budget to fill the positions. </inglise>
<eesti>Mis puudutab punkti 2.2.5 "Autori&otilde;iguse &otilde;petamine ja uurimist&ouml;&ouml;", siis hetkel on Phare 4 MEUR projekti raames plaan eesti keeles v&auml;lja anda k&otilde;igi autori&otilde;iguse ja autori&otilde;igusega kaasnevate &otilde;iguste alaste Eesti v&auml;lislepingute tekstid ning EL direktiivide t&otilde;lked. </eesti>
<inglise>As regards point 2.2.5 "Teaching copyright and research", the texts of all of Estonia's international agreements and translations of EU directives concerning copyright and related rights will be published in Estonian within the framework of the Phare 4MEUR Project. </inglise>
