<eesti>&Uuml;le&uuml;ldine suhtumine piraatlusse. </eesti>
<inglise>General attitudes towards piracy. </inglise>
<eesti>Politsei puhul selle prioriteediks t&otilde;stmine, koolitusvajadus </eesti>
<inglise>Making this a priority with the police, and police training needs. </inglise>
<eesti>Nagu k&auml;esolevas &uuml;levaates juba mainitud, saab politsei tegevust piraatluse t&otilde;kestamises ning intellektuaalse omandi rikkumistes &uuml;ldjoontes pidada positiivseks ning on t&auml;heldada arengut selles osas. </eesti>
<inglise>As previously mentioned in this overview, the activities of the police in combating piracy and regarding the infringement of intellectual property can generally be considered positive and certain progress has been observed. </inglise>
<eesti>Siiski v&otilde;ib tunda politseipoolse huvi ajutist raugemist sagedaste reidide korraldamises ning see on andnud kohe tagasil&ouml;&ouml;gi - j&auml;lle on Kadaka Turul avatud enamus piraattoodanguga kauplevaid bokse. </eesti>
<inglise>However, the interest of the police in organising frequent raids seems to have temporarily decreased somewhat and a setback has occurred instantly - most of the stalls trading in pirated products at Kadaka Market have reopened. </inglise>
<eesti>Seega tuleks kindlasti j&auml;tkata antud initsiatiiviga, mis ennast tegelikult juba m&otilde;ne n&auml;dalaga on &otilde;igustanud ning &auml;sjased arengud on ka kinnitanud, et niipea, kui t&auml;helepanu n&otilde;rgeneb, seavad m&uuml;&uuml;jad ennast j&auml;lle sisse. </eesti>
<inglise>The initiative should therefore definitely continue as it did produce results in just a few weeks and as recent developments confirm that as soon as scrutiny becomes less intense, the traders carry on as before. </inglise>
<eesti>Kindlasti tuleb edaspidigi t&ouml;&ouml;d teha piraatlusevastase v&otilde;itluse prioriteetide hulka t&otilde;stmise osas. </eesti>
<inglise>A lot of work definitely remains to be done to make combating piracy a priority. </inglise>
<eesti>J&auml;tkuvalt on oluliseks osaks seadusi rakendavate institutsioonide koolitamine, mida peaks lisaks juba toimunud ja kindlalt planeeritud &uuml;ritustele veelgi enam korraldama. </eesti>
<inglise>Training the staff at institutions implementing Acts is still of considerable importance and should continue to an even greater extent than those events which have already taken place or are planned. </inglise>
<eesti>Seni on t&otilde;husaks abiks olnud v&auml;lisabiprogrammide finantsvahendid, samuti on initsiatiivi &uuml;les n&auml;idanud esindusorganisatsioonid, aga nii Politseiamet, Tolliamet kui Riigikohus peaks ka ise j&auml;tkama sellealaste koolituste korraldamist. </eesti>
<inglise>So far, financial resources from foreign aid programmes have been extremely helpful and the collective management organisations have shown a deal of initiative, but the Police Board, the Customs Board and the Supreme Court should also continue organising training in the relevant fields themselves. </inglise>
<eesti>M&otilde;tlema peaks ka efektiivsemate koost&ouml;&ouml;v&otilde;imaluste leidmisele tolli- ja politseistruktuuride vahel, sest kahtlemata j&auml;&auml;b tolli v&auml;het&otilde;hus t&ouml;&ouml; olulist lisakoormust teistele seadusi rakendavatele institutsioonidele. </eesti>
<inglise>Expansion of the co-operation between customs and police structures should also be given some thought as the inefficiency of the customs authorities does place additional burdens on other institutions implementing Acts. </inglise>
<eesti>Mis puudutab &uuml;le&uuml;ldist suhtumist, siis sellelgi juhul on vaja j&auml;tkata inimeste laialdast informeerimist esmatasandist. </eesti>
<inglise>As regards general attitudes, extensive dissemination of information to the general public needs to be continued on the primary level. </inglise>
<eesti>Hetkel on j&auml;rjekordse Phare 4MEUR projekti raames koostamisel informatiivne autori&otilde;igusi ja autori&otilde;igusega kaasnevaid &otilde;igusi tutvustav bro&scaron;&uuml;&uuml;r, kuid sarnane algatus ei saa edaspidi j&auml;&auml;da j&auml;llegi ainult v&auml;lisvahendite arvel finantseeritavaks. KOKKUV&Otilde;TE </eesti>
<inglise>An information brochure describing copyright and related rights is currently being prepared within the framework of another Phare 4MEUR Project but, in the future, such initiatives cannot continue to be financed by foreign funds alone. </inglise>
<eesti>K&auml;esoleva materjali kokkuv&otilde;tteks v&otilde;ib &ouml;elda, et kuigi praktiliselt kogu t&ouml;&ouml; Eesti autori&otilde;igusealase seadusandluse rahvusvahelisele tasemele viimiseks tehti &auml;ra 1998 ja 1999 aasta jooksul, on vastavad muudatused just j&otilde;ustunud 2000. aastal - 6. jaanuaril j&otilde;ustusid Euroopa Liidu direktiividel p&otilde;hinevad muudatused meie "Autori&otilde;iguse seadusesse", 28. aprillist alates on Eesti suhtes kehtiv Rooma 1961. a. konventsioon ning 28. maist alates Genfi 1971. a. konventsioon. Seega v&otilde;ib &ouml;elda, et Eestis kehtib n&uuml;&uuml;dsest praktiliselt k&otilde;ikidele hetkel j&otilde;us olevatele autori&otilde;igusealastele rahvusvahelistele normidele vastav seadusandlus ning samav&otilde;rdselt oluline on ka fakt, et oleme n&uuml;&uuml;dsest &uuml;lalnimetatud konventsioonide liikmed ning t&auml;idetud on Euroopa Lepingu Artiklist 66 ja lisast IX tulenevad autori&otilde;igusealased kohustused. </eesti>
<inglise>SUMMARY </inglise>


<eesti>Maikuine initsiatiiv politseipeadirektori korraldusega moodustatud t&ouml;&ouml;grupi poolt tihedate reidide korraldamiseks Kadaka Turule on t&otilde;endanud, et tahtmise korral on v&otilde;imalus piraattoodetega kauplejate tegevuse p&auml;rssimiseks ning l&otilde;puks ka piraatkaubanduse likvideerimiseks t&auml;iesti olemas. Elu on ka kahjuks n&auml;idanud, et aastate jooksul h&auml;sti sisset&ouml;&ouml;tanud piraattoodangu pakkumise s&uuml;steem saab jalad j&auml;lle alla niipea, kui t&auml;helepanu neilt p&ouml;&ouml;rata. </eesti>
<inglise>To sum up this paper, it can be said that although virtually all the work to bring Estonian legislation in the field of copyright to international level carried out during 1998 and 1999, the corresponding amendments have entered into force in 2000 - amendments to the Copyright Act based on European Union directives entered into force on 6 January, the Rome Convention of 1961 applies to Estonia as of 28 April and the Geneva Convention of 1971 as of 28 May. </inglise>
<eesti>Mingil juhul ei saa lubada juba saavutatu k&auml;est &auml;ra andmist. Positiivse tendentsina v&otilde;ib v&auml;lja tuua asjaolu, et 2000. aasta jooksul on huvi autori&otilde;iguste ja autori&otilde;igusega kaasnevate &otilde;iguste vastu suurenenud praktiliselt igal tasemel - tuntakse huvi koolituste ja seminaride vastu, ka ajakirjandus kajastab nimetatud temaatikate sagedamini, kui kunagi varem jne. </eesti>
<inglise>It can therefore be stated that Estonian legislation is now in compliance with virtually all international standards relating to copyright, and the facts that we are now members of these Conventions and that the copyright-related obligations arising from Article 66 and Annex IX of the European Agreement are being performed are equally important. </inglise>
<eesti>J&auml;relikult on ka laiema &uuml;ldsuse poolt hakatud aru saama, et autori&otilde;igusealane temaatika on oluline nii meie siseriiklikul tasandil kui rahvusvaheliste n&otilde;udmiste kontekstis. On juba korraldatud ja ka planeerimisel mitmeid seminare ja koolitusi, v&auml;lisabi projektide raames on plaanis v&auml;lja anda ka informatiivne bro&scaron;&uuml;&uuml;r ja mahukam autori&otilde;igusi ja autori&otilde;igusega kaasnevaid &otilde;igusi puudutavad Eesti v&auml;lislepingute tekstid ning EL direktiivide t&otilde;lked. </eesti>
<inglise>Further amendments to Acts which are still in the draft stage will further decrease the number of minor gaps existing in our legislation (after that only certain requirements arising from the TRIPS Agreement will remain and these will be met upon the entry into force of the new procedural codes which are currently being prepared by the Ministry of Justice). And so, the police, customs authorities and courts do indeed have the entire base they need and on which they can rely for efficient protection of intellectual property rights. </inglise>


<eesti>Tulenevalt punktis 1 nimetatud seaduse j&otilde;ustumisega ning punktis 2 nimetatud Rooma 1961. a. konventsiooni j&otilde;ustumisega Eesti Vabariigi suhtes on Eesti t&auml;itnud Euroopa Lepingu Artiklist 66 ja lisast IX tulenevad autori&otilde;igusealased kohustused. </eesti>
<inglise>The initiative of the working group formed by an order of the national police commissioner in May to organise frequent raids on Kadaka Market has proven that it is certainly possible to obstruct the activities of traders in pirated products and, eventually, to terminate trading in pirated goods altogether. </inglise>
<eesti>(2) Agreement on Trade Related Aspects of Intellectual Property Rights (vt Maailma Kaubandusorganisatsiooni asutamislepingu lisa 1C; ilmunud RT II 1999, 22, I lisavihik "Eesti &Uuml;hinemine Maailma Kaubandusorganisatsiooniga. Dokumendid"). </eesti>
<inglise>Unfortunately, experience time has also shown that the well-oiled piracy machine will make up for lost time as soon as scrutiny under which it is placed is reduced. Under no circumstances can we let what we have already achieved slip away. </inglise>
<eesti>(3) Siin ja edaspidi on Phare 4MEUR projekti puhul viidatud nimetatud projekti toetusel l&auml;bi viidavale alaprojektile No 00/C/166 "Enforcement of EU Intellectual Property Legislation" </eesti>
<inglise>The fact that interest in copyright and related rights has increased on virtually all levels during the year 2000 can be emphasised as a positive indicator - interest is being shown in training and seminars and the relevant issues are being covered by the press more frequently than ever before. </inglise>
<eesti>(4) Euroopa Parlamendi ja N&otilde;ukogu direktiiv siseturu elektroonilise kaubanduse teatavate &otilde;iguslike aspektide kohta (European Parliament and Council Directive on Certain Legal Aspects of Electronic Commerce in the Internal Market) - teenusepakkujaid ja nende vastutust k&auml;sitlevad sellest artiklid 12-15, millist regulatsiooni peakski vastava koost&ouml;&ouml;leppe s&otilde;lmimisel arvestama. </eesti>
<inglise>Apparently the general public is also beginning to understand that copyright issues are of considerable importance both at national level and in the context of international requirements. Several seminars and training sessions have already been organised and further ones are planned for the future, and foreign aid projects are being used to finance publication of an informative brochure and of the texts of all of Estonia's international agreements and translations of EU directives concerning copyright and related rights. </inglise>

